{"title_page": "Tassadit Yacine", "text_new": "{{BLP primary sources|date=March 2020}}\n\n{{Infobox person\n| honorific_prefix   = Professor\n| name               = Tassadit Yacine\n| image              = Tassadit Yacine.jpg\n| caption            = Yacine speaking at a conference in 2015\n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|1949|11|14}}\n| birth_place        = Boudjellil\n| nationality        = Algerian\n| occupation         = Anthropologist\n}}\n\n'''Tassadit Yacine-Titouh''' (14 November 1949 - Boudjellil, Algeria) is an [[anthropologist]] specialising in [[Berber culture]].\n\n== Early life ==\nYacine was born on 14 November 1949, in [[Boudjellil]], in the [[Provinces of Algeria|wilaya]] [[Bejaia Province|Bejaia]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.elmoudjahid.com/fr/actualites/147741|title=Vente-d\u00e9dicace de Tassadit Yacine : Kabylie 1871, L'insurrection : R\u00e9sistance et r\u00e9volte d'une population|website=www.elmoudjahid.com|access-date=2020-03-06}}</ref> Her mother was a housewife and her father an immigrant who was tortured and executed in 1956.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=http://bleu-autour.com/auteur_bleu/tassadit/|title=Tassadit Yacine {{!}} Bleu autour, \u00e9diteur|website=bleu-autour.com|access-date=2020-03-07}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nYacine is Director of Study at [[l'Ecole des Hautes Etudes en Sciences Sociales]] (EHESS)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.franceculture.fr/personne-tassadit-yacine.html|title=Tassadit Yacine : biographie, actualit\u00e9s et \u00e9missions France Culture|website=France Culture|language=fr|access-date=2020-03-06}}</ref> and is also a member of the department of social anthropology at the [[Coll\u00e8ge de France]].<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite journal|last=Romey|first=Alain|date=2009-06-15|title=Pierre Bourdieu - Esquisses alg\u00e9riennes, textes \u00e9dit\u00e9s et pr\u00e9sent\u00e9s par Tassadit Yacine|url=http://journals.openedition.org/cdlm/4716|journal=Cahiers de la M\u00e9diterran\u00e9e|language=fr|issue=78|pages=387\u2013388|issn=0395-9317}}</ref> She directs ''Awal'' (\"The word\") - a journal founded in 1985 in Paris with the Algerian anthropologist [[Mouloud Mammeri]] and the sociologist [[Pierre Bourdieu]] to explore Berber life.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\nYacine's doctoral thesis was entitled ''Productions culturelles et agents de production en kabylie : anthropologie de la culture dans les groupes kabyles 16e-20e siecle,'' which she was awarded a PhD for in 1992 from [[Paris-Sorbonne University]].<ref>{{Cite thesis|title=Productions culturelles et agents de production en kabylie : anthropologie de la culture dans les groupes kabyles 16e-20e siecle|url=http://www.theses.fr/1993PA030091|publisher=Paris 3|date=1992-01-01|degree=thesis|first=Tassadit|last=Yacine}}</ref> Her first degree was in Spanish at the University of Algiers; she graduated for it in 1980.<ref name=\":1\" />\n\n== Research ==\nYacine has written widely on Berber anthropology<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Gelard|first=Marie Luce|date=2011-12-31|title=Tassadit Yacine, Si tu m'aimes, gu\u00e9ris-moi. \u00c9tudes d'ethnologie des affects en Kabylie, Pr\u00e9face de Fran\u00e7oise H\u00e9ritier. Postface de Sherry B. Ortner|url=http://journals.openedition.org/insaniyat/13173|journal=Insaniyat / \u0625\u0646\u0633\u0627\u0646\u064a\u0627\u062a. Revue alg\u00e9rienne d'anthropologie et de sciences sociales|language=fr|issue=54|pages=175\u2013176|issn=1111-2050}}</ref> Her approach to social anthropology combines scientific assessment with oral literature.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Amghar|first=Nabila|date=2001|title=Tassadit Yacine-Titouh, Chacal ou la ruse des domin\u00e9s : aux origines du malaise culturel des intellectuels alg\u00e9riens, 2001|url=https://www.persee.fr/doc/homig_1142-852x_2001_num_1232_1_5291_t1_0145_0000_6|journal=Hommes & Migrations|volume=1232|issue=1|pages=145\u2013146}}</ref> She is an expert on the work of Bourdieu, placing his experiences in Algeria as a central influence on his philosophy.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Meynier|first=Gilbert|date=2009-11-27|title=Tassadit Yacine (textes \u00e9dit\u00e9s et pr\u00e9sent\u00e9s par), Pierre Bourdieu, Esquisses alg\u00e9riennes, Paris, Seuil (coll. Liber), 2008, 414 p.|url=http://journals.openedition.org/remmm/6322|journal=Revue des mondes musulmans et de la M\u00e9diterran\u00e9e|language=fr|issue=126|issn=0997-1327}}</ref> She edited the diaries of [[Jean Amrouche]], enabling greater understanding of his influence on literature.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Romey|first=Alain|date=2010-06-15|title=Jean El Mouhoub Amrouche - Journal (1928-1962), texte \u00e9dit\u00e9 par Tassadit Yacine Titouh|url=http://journals.openedition.org/cdlm/5351|journal=Cahiers de la M\u00e9diterran\u00e9e|language=fr|issue=80|pages=289\u2013292|issn=0395-9317}}</ref> She led the colloquium following the death of [[Rabah Belamri]], which re-examined, as well as playing tribute to, his role in literary culture in the Maghreb.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Ammar Khodja|first=Soumya|date=2001|title=TASSADIT Yacine (sous la direction de), Enracinement culturel et r\u00f4le des m\u00e9diateurs au Maghreb, L'exemple de Rabah Belamri, L'Harmattan-Awal, 2000, 164 p.|url=https://www.erudit.org/en/journals/ela/1900-v1-n1-ela03261/1041903ar/abstract/|journal=\u00c9tudes litt\u00e9raires africaines|language=fr|volume=|issue=11|pages=82\u201383|doi=10.7202/1041903ar|issn=0769-4563|via=}}</ref> She edited a collection of Bourdieu's writings, where Yacine placed his work in its Algerian political contexts.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Goodman|first=Jane E.|date=2015|title=Pierre Bourdieu, Algerian Sketches. Tassadit Yacine, ed., David Fernbach, trans. Malden, Mass.: Polity Press, 2013, 390 pp.|journal=Comparative Studies in Society and History|language=en|volume=57|issue=2|pages=595\u2013597|doi=10.1017/S0010417515000158|issn=0010-4175}}</ref>\n\nShe is an expert on the life of [[Berbers|Berber peoples]] and has published and spoken widely on the subject, especially how Arabic culture and language has eroded Amazigh identities over the course of the twentieth century.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://user.eng.umd.edu/~sellami/DEC95/culture.html|title=Amazigh Voice, December 1995 - March 1996 issue|website=user.eng.umd.edu|access-date=2019-12-04}}</ref> Yacine has studied [[kabyle language]] and Berber literary cultures in particular.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.persee.fr/authority/264646|title=Tassadit, Yacine - Pers\u00e9e|website=www.persee.fr|access-date=2020-03-07}}</ref> She is also an authority on how gender intersects with the erosion of cultural identities in Amazigh culture, using a Freudian framework for cultural analysis.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Giafferi-Dombre|first=Natacha|date=2009-01-01|title=Tassadit Yacine-Titouh, Si tu m'aimes, gu\u00e9ris-moi !|url=http://journals.openedition.org/lhomme/28738|journal=L'Homme. Revue fran\u00e7aise d'anthropologie|language=fr|issue=190|pages=232\u2013233|issn=0439-4216}}</ref> This work was built on in a subsequent thesis by Terhi Lehtinen.<ref>{{Cite thesis|title=Nation \u00e0 la marge de l'Etat : la construction identaire du Mouvement Culturel Amazigh dans l'espace national marocain et au-del\u00e0 des fronti\u00e8res \u00e9tatiques|url=http://www.theses.fr/2003EHES0133|publisher=Paris, EHESS|date=2003-01-01|degree=thesis|first=Terhi|last=Lehtinen}}</ref> Two of her most significant academic works are seen to be: Ch''acal ou la ruse des domin\u00e9s'' (2001) and ''Si tu m'aimes, gu\u00e9ris-moi'' (2006).<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Alonso|first=Maria \u00c0ngels Roque|date=2016|title=Entrevista a Tassadit Yacine|url=https://dialnet.unirioja.es/servlet/articulo?codigo=5526318|journal=Quaderns de la Mediterr\u00e0nia = Cuadernos del Mediterr\u00e1neo|issue=23|pages=307\u2013318|issn=1577-9297}}</ref> In the latter book, Yacine places Berber culture in its wider Mediterranean context, as well as transcending the traditional distinction between oral and written cultures.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Bonte|first=Pierre|date=2009-01-01|title=Tassadit Yacine-Titouh, Si tu m'aimes, gu\u00e9ris-moi !. Paris, \u00c9d. de la Maison des sciences de l'homme, 2006, 175 pages|url=http://journals.openedition.org/lhomme/28736|journal=L'Homme. Revue fran\u00e7aise d'anthropologie|language=fr|issue=190|pages=229\u2013231|issn=0439-4216}}</ref>{{Wikiquote|it:Tassadit_Yacine}}[[File:Tassadit_Yacine_(21e_Maghreb_des_Livres,_Paris,_7_et_8_f\u00e9vrier_2015).jpg|thumb|Tassadit Yacine (21e Maghreb des Livres, Paris, 7 et 8 f\u00e9vrier 2015)]]\n\n=== Monographs ===\n\n* 1987 - ''L'izli ou l'amour chant\u00e9 en kabyle'', Pr\u00e9face de Pierre Bourdieu, Paris, MSH - <small>({{ISBN|273510253X}}).</small><ref>{{Cite book|title=L'izli, ou, L'amour chant\u00e9 en kabyle|last=Yacine-Titouh, Tassadit.|date=1988|publisher=Editions de la Maison des sciences de l'homme|others=Bourdieu, Pierre, 1930-2002|isbn=2-7351-0253-X|location=Paris|oclc=20507401}}</ref>\n* 1989 - ''A\u00eft Menguellet chante... Chansons berb\u00e8res contemporaines'', Paris, La D\u00e9couverte - <small>({{ISBN|2707118877}})</small>. Pr\u00e9face de Kateb Yacine.<ref>{{Cite book|title=A\u00eft Menguellet chante-- : chansons berb\u00e8res contemporaines : textes berb\u00e8res et fran\u00e7ais|last=A\u00eft Menguellet, Lounis, 1950-|date=1989|publisher=La D\u00e9couverte|others=Yacine-Titouh, Tassadit.|isbn=2-7071-1887-7|location=Paris|oclc=21872768}}</ref>\n* 1992 - ''Les Kabyles. \u00c9l\u00e9ments pour la compr\u00e9hension de l'identit\u00e9 berb\u00e8re en Alg\u00e9rie'', Paris, GDM - <small>({{ISBN|2-906589-13-6}})</small>.<ref>{{Cite book|title=Les Kabyles : \u00e9l\u00e9ments pour la compr\u00e9hension de l'identit\u00e9 berb\u00e8re en Alg\u00e9rie|date=1992|publisher=Groupement pour le droits des minorit\u00e9s|others=Yacine-Titouh, Tassadit.|isbn=2-906589-13-6|location=Paris|oclc=28248443}}</ref>\n* 1992 - ''Amour, phantasmes et soci\u00e9t\u00e9s en Afrique du Nord et au Sahara'', Paris, L'Harmattan - <small>({{ISBN|2738417620}}).</small><ref>{{Cite book|title=Amour, phantasmes et soci\u00e9t\u00e9s en Afrique du Nord et au Sahara : actes du colloque international des 14-15-16 juin 1989|date=1992|publisher=L'Harmattan|others=Mammeri, Mouloud, 1917-1989., Yacine-Titouh, Tassadit., Centre d'\u00e9tudes et de recherches Amazigh (France)|isbn=2-7384-1762-0|location=Paris|oclc=30702206}}</ref>\n* 1993 - ''Les voleurs de feu'', Paris, La D\u00e9couverte - <small>({{ISBN|2707122890}})</small>.<ref>{{Cite book|title=Les voleurs de feu : \u00e9l\u00e9ments d'une anthropologie sociale et culturelle de l'Alg\u00e9rie|last=Yacine-Titouh, Tassadit.|date=1993|publisher=La D\u00e9couverte|isbn=2-7071-2289-0|location=Paris|oclc=30918729}}</ref>\n* 1995 - ''Ch\u00e9rif Kheddam ou l'amour de l'art'', Paris, La D\u00e9couverte- <small>({{ISBN|2707124192}})</small>.<ref>{{Cite book|title=Ch\u00e9rif Kheddam, ou, L'amour de l'art : chansons berb\u00e8res contemporaines|last=Yacine-Titouh, Tassadit.|date=1995|publisher=La D\u00e9couverte|isbn=2-7071-2419-2|location=Paris|oclc=32825250}}</ref>\n* 1995 \u2013 ''Pi\u00e8ge ou le combat d'une femme alg\u00e9rienne: Essai d'anthropologie de la souffrance'', Paris, Awal/Publisud - <small>({{ISBN|2866007581}})</small>.<ref>{{Cite book|title=Pi\u00e8ge, ou, Le combat d'une femme alg\u00e9rienne : essai d'anthropologie de la souffrance|last=Yacine-Titouh, Tassadit.|date=1995|publisher=Publisud|others=Nouara, 1939-|isbn=2-86600-758-1|location=Paris|oclc=35086286}}</ref>\n*1996 \u2013 ''Nuara. Quaderno poetico di una donna cabila'' (\u00e9d. italienne par les soins de Domenico Canciani), Edizioni Lavoro - <small>({{ISBN|978-8879107181}}).</small><ref>{{Cite book|title=Nuara : quaderno poetico di una donna cabila|last=Nuara.|date=1996|publisher=Lavoro|others=Yacine, Tassadit., Canciani, Domenico., Zanzottera, Bruno.|isbn=88-7910-718-6|location=Roma|oclc=898501363}}</ref>\n* 2001 - ''Chacal ou la ruse des domin\u00e9s'', Paris, La D\u00e9couverte - <small>({{ISBN|2707133957}})</small>.<ref>{{Cite book|title=Chacal ou la ruse des domin\u00e9s : aux origines du malaise culturel des intellectuels alg\u00e9riens|last=Yacine, Tassadit, 1949-|date=2001|publisher=La D\u00e9couverte|isbn=2-7071-3395-7|location=Paris|oclc=406939773}}</ref>\n* 2003 - ''Jean Amrouche, l'\u00e9ternel exil\u00e9''. Antologia di testi (1939 - 1950), Parigi, \u00c9ditions Awal-IBIS Press - <small>({{ISBN|2910728250}})</small>.<ref>{{Cite book|title=Jean Amrouche, l'\u00e9ternel exil\u00e9 : choix de textes, 1939-1950|last=Amrouche, Jean, 1906-1962.|date=2002|publisher=Awal|others=Yacine, Tassadit, 1949- ..., Impr. Jouve)|isbn=2-910728-25-0|location=Paris|oclc=469134600}}</ref>\n* 2006 - ''Si tu m'aimes, gu\u00e9ris moi: \u00e9tudes d'ethnologie des affects en Kabylie'', Paris, Maison des sciences de l'homme - <small>({{ISBN|2735110869}})</small>.<ref>{{Cite book|title=Si tu m'aimes, gu\u00e9ris-moi : \u00e9tudes d'ethnologie des affects en Kabylie|last=Yacine-Titouh, Tassadit.|date=2006|publisher=Maison des sciences de l'homme|isbn=2-7351-1086-9|location=Paris|oclc=300339475}}</ref>\n* 2008 - Pierre Bourdieu, ''Esquisses alg\u00e9riennes'', textes \u00e9dit\u00e9s et pr\u00e9sent\u00e9s par Tassadit Yacine, Paris, Seuil - <small>({{ISBN|978-2020982863}}).</small><ref>{{Cite book|title=Esquisses alg\u00e9riennes|last=Bourdieu, Pierre, 1930-2002.|date=2008|publisher=Seuil|others=Yacine-Titouh, Tassadit.|isbn=978-2-02-098286-3|location=Paris|oclc=269318025}}</ref>\n* 2009 - Jean El Mouhoub Amrouche, ''Journal (1928-1962)'', texte \u00e9dit\u00e9 par Tassadit Yacine Titouh, Paris, Non Lieu - <small>({{ISBN|978-2352700562}}).</small><ref>{{Cite book|title=Journal : 1928-1962|last=Amrouche, Jean, 1906-1962.|date=2009|publisher=Non-lieu|others=Yacine-Titouh, Tassadit.|isbn=978-2-35270-056-2|location=Paris|oclc=432297227}}</ref>\n* 2011 - ''Le retour de Jugurtha. Amrouche dans la lutte : du racisme de la colonisation'', Tizi Ouzou, Passerelles \u00c9ditions - <small>({{ISBN|9789931905103}}).</small><ref>{{Cite book|title=Le retour de Jugurtha Amrouche dans la lutte du racisme de la colonisation|last=Yacine, Tassadit, (1949- ...)|date=2011|publisher=Passerelles|isbn=978-9931-9051-0-3|location=Alger|oclc=949119713}}</ref>\n\nA full bibliography of Yacine's publications can be found on the [http://las.ehess.fr/index.php?211 EHESS] site.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://las.ehess.fr/index.php?211|title=Tassadit Yacine|last=|first=|date=|website=|language=fr|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-03-07}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n<references />\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Yacine, Tassadit}}\n[[Category:1949 births]]\n[[Category:Algerian women]]\n[[Category:Archaeologists]]\n[[Category:Anthropologists]]\n[[Category:Kabyle people]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Algerian Berber feminists]]\n", "text_old": "{{BLP primary sources|date=March 2020}}\n\n{{Infobox person\n| honorific_prefix   = Professor\n| name               = Tassadit Yacine\n| image              = Tassadit Yacine.jpg\n| caption            = Yacine speaking at a conference in 2015\n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|1949|11|14}}\n| birth_place        = Boudjellil\n| nationality        = Algerian\n| occupation         = Anthropologist\n}}\n\n'''Tassadit Yacine-Titouh''' (14 November 1949 - Boudjellil, Algeria) is an [[anthropologist]] specialising in [[Berber culture]].\n\n== Early life ==\nYacine was born on 14 November 1949, in [[Boudjellil]], in the [[Provinces of Algeria|wilaya]] [[Bejaia Province|Bejaia]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.elmoudjahid.com/fr/actualites/147741|title=Vente-d\u00e9dicace de Tassadit Yacine : Kabylie 1871, L'insurrection : R\u00e9sistance et r\u00e9volte d'une population|website=www.elmoudjahid.com|access-date=2020-03-06}}</ref> Her mother was a housewife and her father an immigrant who was tortured and executed in 1956.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=http://bleu-autour.com/auteur_bleu/tassadit/|title=Tassadit Yacine {{!}} Bleu autour, \u00e9diteur|website=bleu-autour.com|access-date=2020-03-07}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nYacine is Director of Study at [[l'Ecole des Hautes Etudes en Sciences Sociales]] (EHESS)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.franceculture.fr/personne-tassadit-yacine.html|title=Tassadit Yacine : biographie, actualit\u00e9s et \u00e9missions France Culture|website=France Culture|language=fr|access-date=2020-03-06}}</ref> and is also a member of the department of social anthropology at the [[Coll\u00e8ge de France]].<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite journal|last=Romey|first=Alain|date=2009-06-15|title=Pierre Bourdieu - Esquisses alg\u00e9riennes, textes \u00e9dit\u00e9s et pr\u00e9sent\u00e9s par Tassadit Yacine|url=http://journals.openedition.org/cdlm/4716|journal=Cahiers de la M\u00e9diterran\u00e9e|language=fr|issue=78|pages=387\u2013388|issn=0395-9317}}</ref> She directs ''Awal'' (\"The word\") - a journal founded in 1985 in Paris with the Algerian anthropologist [[Mouloud Mammeri]] and the sociologist [[Pierre Bourdieu]] to explore Berber life.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\nYacine's doctoral thesis was entitled ''Productions culturelles et agents de production en kabylie : anthropologie de la culture dans les groupes kabyles 16e-20e siecle,'' which she was awarded a PhD for in 1992 from [[Paris-Sorbonne University]].<ref>{{Cite thesis|title=Productions culturelles et agents de production en kabylie : anthropologie de la culture dans les groupes kabyles 16e-20e siecle|url=http://www.theses.fr/1993PA030091|publisher=Paris 3|date=1992-01-01|degree=thesis|first=Tassadit|last=Yacine}}</ref> Her first degree was in Spanish at the University of Algiers; she graduated for it in 1980.<ref name=\":1\" />\n\n== Research ==\nYacine has written widely on Berber anthropology<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Gelard|first=Marie Luce|date=2011-12-31|title=Tassadit Yacine, Si tu m'aimes, gu\u00e9ris-moi. \u00c9tudes d'ethnologie des affects en Kabylie, Pr\u00e9face de Fran\u00e7oise H\u00e9ritier. Postface de Sherry B. Ortner|url=http://journals.openedition.org/insaniyat/13173|journal=Insaniyat / \u0625\u0646\u0633\u0627\u0646\u064a\u0627\u062a. Revue alg\u00e9rienne d'anthropologie et de sciences sociales|language=fr|issue=54|pages=175\u2013176|issn=1111-2050}}</ref> Her approach to social anthropology combines scientific assessment with oral literature.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Amghar|first=Nabila|date=2001|title=Tassadit Yacine-Titouh, Chacal ou la ruse des domin\u00e9s : aux origines du malaise culturel des intellectuels alg\u00e9riens, 2001|url=https://www.persee.fr/doc/homig_1142-852x_2001_num_1232_1_5291_t1_0145_0000_6|journal=Hommes & Migrations|volume=1232|issue=1|pages=145\u2013146}}</ref> She is an expert on the work of Bourdieu, placing his experiences in Algeria as a central influence on his philosophy.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Meynier|first=Gilbert|date=2009-11-27|title=Tassadit Yacine (textes \u00e9dit\u00e9s et pr\u00e9sent\u00e9s par), Pierre Bourdieu, Esquisses alg\u00e9riennes, Paris, Seuil (coll. Liber), 2008, 414 p.|url=http://journals.openedition.org/remmm/6322|journal=Revue des mondes musulmans et de la M\u00e9diterran\u00e9e|language=fr|issue=126|issn=0997-1327}}</ref> She edited the diaries of [[Jean Amrouche]], enabling greater understanding of his influence on literature.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Romey|first=Alain|date=2010-06-15|title=Jean El Mouhoub Amrouche - Journal (1928-1962), texte \u00e9dit\u00e9 par Tassadit Yacine Titouh|url=http://journals.openedition.org/cdlm/5351|journal=Cahiers de la M\u00e9diterran\u00e9e|language=fr|issue=80|pages=289\u2013292|issn=0395-9317}}</ref> She led the colloquium following the death of [[Rabah Belamri]], which re-examined, as well as playing tribute to, his role in literary culture in the Maghreb.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Ammar Khodja|first=Soumya|date=2001|title=TASSADIT Yacine (sous la direction de), Enracinement culturel et r\u00f4le des m\u00e9diateurs au Maghreb, L'exemple de Rabah Belamri, L'Harmattan-Awal, 2000, 164 p.|url=https://www.erudit.org/en/journals/ela/1900-v1-n1-ela03261/1041903ar/abstract/|journal=\u00c9tudes litt\u00e9raires africaines|language=fr|volume=|issue=11|pages=82\u201383|doi=10.7202/1041903ar|issn=0769-4563|via=}}</ref> She edited a collection of Bourdieu's writings, where Yacine placed his work in its Algerian political contexts.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Goodman|first=Jane E.|date=2015|title=Pierre Bourdieu, Algerian Sketches. Tassadit Yacine, ed., David Fernbach, trans. Malden, Mass.: Polity Press, 2013, 390 pp.|journal=Comparative Studies in Society and History|language=en|volume=57|issue=2|pages=595\u2013597|doi=10.1017/S0010417515000158|issn=0010-4175}}</ref>\n\nShe is an expert on the life of [[Berbers|Berber peoples]] and has published and spoken widely on the subject, especially how Arabic culture and language has eroded Amazigh identities over the course of the twentieth century.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://user.eng.umd.edu/~sellami/DEC95/culture.html|title=Amazigh Voice, December 1995 - March 1996 issue|website=user.eng.umd.edu|access-date=2019-12-04}}</ref> Yacine has studied [[kabyle language]] and Berber literary cultures in particular.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.persee.fr/authority/264646|title=Tassadit, Yacine - Pers\u00e9e|website=www.persee.fr|access-date=2020-03-07}}</ref> She is also an authority on how gender intersects with the erosion of cultural identities in Amazigh culture, using a Freudian framework for cultural analysis.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Giafferi-Dombre|first=Natacha|date=2009-01-01|title=Tassadit Yacine-Titouh, Si tu m'aimes, gu\u00e9ris-moi !|url=http://journals.openedition.org/lhomme/28738|journal=L'Homme. Revue fran\u00e7aise d'anthropologie|language=fr|issue=190|pages=232\u2013233|issn=0439-4216}}</ref> This work was built on in a subsequent thesis by Terhi Lehtinen.<ref>{{Cite thesis|title=Nation \u00e0 la marge de l'Etat : la construction identaire du Mouvement Culturel Amazigh dans l'espace national marocain et au-del\u00e0 des fronti\u00e8res \u00e9tatiques|url=http://www.theses.fr/2003EHES0133|publisher=Paris, EHESS|date=2003-01-01|degree=thesis|first=Terhi|last=Lehtinen}}</ref> Two of her most significant academic works are seen to be: Ch''acal ou la ruse des domin\u00e9s'' (2001) and ''Si tu m'aimes, gu\u00e9ris-moi'' (2006).<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Alonso|first=Maria \u00c0ngels Roque|date=2016|title=Entrevista a Tassadit Yacine|url=https://dialnet.unirioja.es/servlet/articulo?codigo=5526318|journal=Quaderns de la Mediterr\u00e0nia = Cuadernos del Mediterr\u00e1neo|issue=23|pages=307\u2013318|issn=1577-9297}}</ref> In the latter book, Yacine places Berber culture in its wider Mediterranean context, as well as transcending the traditional distinction between oral and written cultures.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Bonte|first=Pierre|date=2009-01-01|title=Tassadit Yacine-Titouh, Si tu m'aimes, gu\u00e9ris-moi !. Paris, \u00c9d. de la Maison des sciences de l'homme, 2006, 175 pages|url=http://journals.openedition.org/lhomme/28736|journal=L'Homme. Revue fran\u00e7aise d'anthropologie|language=fr|issue=190|pages=229\u2013231|issn=0439-4216}}</ref>{{Wikiquote|it:Tassadit_Yacine}}[[File:Tassadit_Yacine_(21e_Maghreb_des_Livres,_Paris,_7_et_8_f\u00e9vrier_2015).jpg|thumb|Tassadit Yacine (21e Maghreb des Livres, Paris, 7 et 8 f\u00e9vrier 2015)]]\n\n=== Monographs ===\n\n* 1987 - ''L'izli ou l'amour chant\u00e9 en kabyle'', Pr\u00e9face de Pierre Bourdieu, Paris, MSH - <small>({{ISBN|273510253X}}).</small><ref>{{Cite book|title=L'izli, ou, L'amour chant\u00e9 en kabyle|last=Yacine-Titouh, Tassadit.|date=1988|publisher=Editions de la Maison des sciences de l'homme|others=Bourdieu, Pierre, 1930-2002|isbn=2-7351-0253-X|location=Paris|oclc=20507401}}</ref>\n* 1989 - ''A\u00eft Menguellet chante... Chansons berb\u00e8res contemporaines'', Paris, La D\u00e9couverte - <small>({{ISBN|2707118877}})</small>. Pr\u00e9face de Kateb Yacine.<ref>{{Cite book|title=A\u00eft Menguellet chante-- : chansons berb\u00e8res contemporaines : textes berb\u00e8res et fran\u00e7ais|last=A\u00eft Menguellet, Lounis, 1950-|date=1989|publisher=La D\u00e9couverte|others=Yacine-Titouh, Tassadit.|isbn=2-7071-1887-7|location=Paris|oclc=21872768}}</ref>\n* 1992 - ''Les Kabyles. \u00c9l\u00e9ments pour la compr\u00e9hension de l'identit\u00e9 berb\u00e8re en Alg\u00e9rie'', Paris, GDM - <small>({{ISBN|2-906589-13-6}})</small>.<ref>{{Cite book|title=Les Kabyles : \u00e9l\u00e9ments pour la compr\u00e9hension de l'identit\u00e9 berb\u00e8re en Alg\u00e9rie|date=1992|publisher=Groupement pour le droits des minorit\u00e9s|others=Yacine-Titouh, Tassadit.|isbn=2-906589-13-6|location=Paris|oclc=28248443}}</ref>\n* 1992 - ''Amour, phantasmes et soci\u00e9t\u00e9s en Afrique du Nord et au Sahara'', Paris, L'Harmattan - <small>({{ISBN|2738417620}}).</small><ref>{{Cite book|title=Amour, phantasmes et soci\u00e9t\u00e9s en Afrique du Nord et au Sahara : actes du colloque international des 14-15-16 juin 1989|date=1992|publisher=L'Harmattan|others=Mammeri, Mouloud, 1917-1989., Yacine-Titouh, Tassadit., Centre d'\u00e9tudes et de recherches Amazigh (France)|isbn=2-7384-1762-0|location=Paris|oclc=30702206}}</ref>\n* 1993 - ''Les voleurs de feu'', Paris, La D\u00e9couverte - <small>({{ISBN|2707122890}})</small>.<ref>{{Cite book|title=Les voleurs de feu : \u00e9l\u00e9ments d'une anthropologie sociale et culturelle de l'Alg\u00e9rie|last=Yacine-Titouh, Tassadit.|date=1993|publisher=La D\u00e9couverte|isbn=2-7071-2289-0|location=Paris|oclc=30918729}}</ref>\n* 1995 - ''Ch\u00e9rif Kheddam ou l'amour de l'art'', Paris, La D\u00e9couverte- <small>({{ISBN|2707124192}})</small>.<ref>{{Cite book|title=Ch\u00e9rif Kheddam, ou, L'amour de l'art : chansons berb\u00e8res contemporaines|last=Yacine-Titouh, Tassadit.|date=1995|publisher=La D\u00e9couverte|isbn=2-7071-2419-2|location=Paris|oclc=32825250}}</ref>\n* 1995 \u2013 ''Pi\u00e8ge ou le combat d'une femme alg\u00e9rienne: Essai d'anthropologie de la souffrance'', Paris, Awal/Publisud - <small>({{ISBN|2866007581}})</small>.<ref>{{Cite book|title=Pi\u00e8ge, ou, Le combat d'une femme alg\u00e9rienne : essai d'anthropologie de la souffrance|last=Yacine-Titouh, Tassadit.|date=1995|publisher=Publisud|others=Nouara, 1939-|isbn=2-86600-758-1|location=Paris|oclc=35086286}}</ref>\n*1996 \u2013 ''Nuara. Quaderno poetico di una donna cabila'' (\u00e9d. italienne par les soins de Domenico Canciani), Edizioni Lavoro - <small>({{ISBN|978-8879107181}}).</small><ref>{{Cite book|title=Nuara : quaderno poetico di una donna cabila|last=Nuara.|date=1996|publisher=Lavoro|others=Yacine, Tassadit., Canciani, Domenico., Zanzottera, Bruno.|isbn=88-7910-718-6|location=Roma|oclc=898501363}}</ref>\n* 2001 - ''Chacal ou la ruse des domin\u00e9s'', Paris, La D\u00e9couverte - <small>({{ISBN|2707133957}})</small>.<ref>{{Cite book|title=Chacal ou la ruse des domin\u00e9s : aux origines du malaise culturel des intellectuels alg\u00e9riens|last=Yacine, Tassadit, 1949-|date=2001|publisher=La D\u00e9couverte|isbn=2-7071-3395-7|location=Paris|oclc=406939773}}</ref>\n* 2003 - ''Jean Amrouche, l'\u00e9ternel exil\u00e9''. Antologia di testi (1939 - 1950), Parigi, \u00c9ditions Awal-IBIS Press - <small>({{ISBN|2910728250}})</small>.<ref>{{Cite book|title=Jean Amrouche, l'\u00e9ternel exil\u00e9 : choix de textes, 1939-1950|last=Amrouche, Jean, 1906-1962.|date=2002|publisher=Awal|others=Yacine, Tassadit, 1949- ..., Impr. Jouve)|isbn=2-910728-25-0|location=Paris|oclc=469134600}}</ref>\n* 2006 - ''Si tu m'aimes, gu\u00e9ris moi: \u00e9tudes d'ethnologie des affects en Kabylie'', Paris, Maison des sciences de l'homme - <small>({{ISBN|2735110869}})</small>.<ref>{{Cite book|title=Si tu m'aimes, gu\u00e9ris-moi : \u00e9tudes d'ethnologie des affects en Kabylie|last=Yacine-Titouh, Tassadit.|date=2006|publisher=Maison des sciences de l'homme|isbn=2-7351-1086-9|location=Paris|oclc=300339475}}</ref>\n* 2008 - Pierre Bourdieu, ''Esquisses alg\u00e9riennes'', textes \u00e9dit\u00e9s et pr\u00e9sent\u00e9s par Tassadit Yacine, Paris, Seuil - <small>({{ISBN|978-2020982863}}).</small><ref>{{Cite book|title=Esquisses alg\u00e9riennes|last=Bourdieu, Pierre, 1930-2002.|date=2008|publisher=Seuil|others=Yacine-Titouh, Tassadit.|isbn=978-2-02-098286-3|location=Paris|oclc=269318025}}</ref>\n* 2009 - Jean El Mouhoub Amrouche, ''Journal (1928-1962)'', texte \u00e9dit\u00e9 par Tassadit Yacine Titouh, Paris, Non Lieu - <small>({{ISBN|978-2352700562}}).</small><ref>{{Cite book|title=Journal : 1928-1962|last=Amrouche, Jean, 1906-1962.|date=2009|publisher=Non-lieu|others=Yacine-Titouh, Tassadit.|isbn=978-2-35270-056-2|location=Paris|oclc=432297227}}</ref>\n* 2011 - ''Le retour de Jugurtha. Amrouche dans la lutte : du racisme de la colonisation'', Tizi Ouzou, Passerelles \u00c9ditions - <small>({{ISBN|9789931905103}}).</small><ref>{{Cite book|title=Le retour de Jugurtha Amrouche dans la lutte du racisme de la colonisation|last=Yacine, Tassadit, (1949- ...)|date=2011|publisher=Passerelles|isbn=978-9931-9051-0-3|location=Alger|oclc=949119713}}</ref>\n\nA full bibliogrpahy of Yacine's publications can be found on the [http://las.ehess.fr/index.php?211 EHESS] site.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://las.ehess.fr/index.php?211|title=Tassadit Yacine|last=|first=|date=|website=|language=fr|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-03-07}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n<references />\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Yacine, Tassadit}}\n[[Category:1949 births]]\n[[Category:Algerian women]]\n[[Category:Archaeologists]]\n[[Category:Anthropologists]]\n[[Category:Kabyle people]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Algerian Berber feminists]]\n", "name_user": "Bellowhead678", "label": "safe", "comment": "bibliogrpahy->bibliography -Fix a typo in one click", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tassadit_Yacine"}
{"title_page": "Beyond Silence (1996 film)", "text_new": "{{short description|1996 film}}\n{{use dmy dates|date=October 2015}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name             = Jenseits der Stille\n| image            =\n| director         = [[Caroline Link]]\n| writer           = {{ubl|Caroline Link|[[Beth Serlin]]}}\n| starring       = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Sylvie Testud]]\n* [[Howie Seago]]\n* [[Emmanuelle Laborit]]\n* [[Sibylle Canonica]]\n* [[Matthias Habich]]\n* Hansa Czypionka\n* Tatjana Trieb}}\n| producer         = {{ubl|[[Jakob Claussen]]|[[Thomas W\u00f6bke]]|[[Luggi Waldleitner]]}}\n| released         = {{film date|1996|12|19|df=y}}\n| runtime          = 112 minutes\n| language         = {{ubl|German|[[German Sign Language]]}}\n| budget           =\n| cinematography   = [[Gernot Roll]]\n| music            = [[Niki Reiser]]\n| editing          = [[Patricia Rommel]]\n| country          = Germany\n| gross            = $11.5 million<ref>http://www.jpbox-office.com/fichfilm.php?id=3318</ref>\n}}\n'''''Beyond Silence''''' ({{lang-de|'''Jenseits der Stille'''}}) is a 1996 German film directed by [[Caroline Link]]. The film was nominated for the [[Academy Award for Best Foreign Language Film]] at the [[70th Academy Awards]].<ref name=\"Oscars1998\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.oscars.org/oscars/ceremonies/1998 |title=The 70th Academy Awards (1998) Nominees and Winners |accessdate=13 October 2015 |work=oscars.org}}</ref>\n\n==Plot==\nThe film tells the story of Lara, who grows up as the daughter of [[deaf]] parents, Martin and Kai. Lara herself is hearing and is fluent in [[sign language]]. Even as a young child, she serves as an [[interpreter]] for her parents in many situations, such as credit negotiations at the bank as well as her own parent-teacher conference, although not always completely truthfully.\n\nLara receives a [[clarinet]] for Christmas from Clarissa, her father's sister and an enthusiastic musician. Lara discovers the world of music, where her parents cannot follow her. In the years that follow, she is discovered to be a talented clarinet player.\n\nAfter Kai is killed in a bicycle accident, Lara's grieving father feels abandoned. When 18-year-old Lara wants to study at a music conservatory in Berlin, the family seems to break apart. The ending seems to reconcile it all: Martin tries to understand the love of music that his daughter feels, and the film comes to a careful reunion between him and Lara.\n\n== Cast ==\n{{cast listing|\n* [[Sylvie Testud]] as Lara\n* Tatjana Trieb as young Lara\n* [[Howie Seago]] as Martin\n* [[Emmanuelle Laborit]] as Kai\n* [[Sibylle Canonica]] as Clarissa\n* [[Matthias Habich]] as Gregor (Clarissa's husband)\n* Alexandra Bolz as Marie\n* Hansa Czypionka as Tom\n* [[Doris Schade]] as Lilli\n* [[Horst Sachtleben]] as Robert\n* Hubert Mulzer as Mister G\u00e4rtner\n* [[Birge Schade]] as Miss Mertens\n* [[Stephan Kampwirth]] as Bank Manager\n}}\n\n==Reviews==\n''Beyond Silence'' has an 83% approval rating on [[Rotten Tomatoes]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/beyond_silence/ |title=Beyond Silence (1996) |publisher=Rotten Tomatoes |accessdate=January 10, 2017}}</ref>\n* \"A successful film debut of a graduate of the Munich Film Academy. The film is a sensible presentation of the problem of the handicapped as well as the universal theme of the self discovery of a young woman and the plea for understanding and openness about seemingly disproportionate experiences.\" (film-dienst 25/1996)\n* \"Whoever would like to find out how loud the snow is and how the sounds of a clarinet can enchant people, should not allow themselves to miss this film: a German production which takes up extraordinary themes across the relationship-comedy and tells the story about saying goodbye to one's childhood with gentle humor and an idiosyncratic aesthetic.\" (Fischer Film Almanach, 1997)\n* \"A film that allows silence to become music and has found strength in the balance between laughing and crying, happiness and pain. \"Jenseits der Stille\" is memorable among German productions, and excellently cast. (Dirk Jasper FilmLexikon)\n* \"Thanks to good casting for all roles and assured acting performances under its direction, this [film is] a successful journey into the world of the deaf, with all its problems of social integration and family conflict.\" (FBW Langfilme)\n\n==Accolades==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Award !! Category !! Recipient !! Result\n|-\n| rowspan=16| 1997\n| rowspan=2| [[Bavarian Film Awards]]\n| [[Bavarian Film Awards (Best Director)|Best Director]]\n| [[Caroline Link]]\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[Bavarian Film Awards (Best Film Score)|Best Film Score]]\n| [[Niki Reiser]]\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| rowspan=2| [[Chicago International Film Festival]]\n| Special Mention\n| Caroline Link\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Best Film\n| Caroline Link\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=5| [[Deutscher Filmpreis]]\n| Best Performance by an Actress in a Leading Role\n| [[Sylvie Testud]]\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Best Editing\n| Niki Reiser \n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Outstanding Feature Film\n| Caroline Link\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Best Performance by an Actress in a Supporting Role \n| [[Emmanuelle Laborit]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Best Direction\n| Caroline Link\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Guild of German Art House Cinemas\n| German Film\n| Caroline Link\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[Palm Springs International Film Festival]]\n| Best Foreign Language Film\n| Caroline Link\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=2| [[Tokyo International Film Festival]]\n| Best Screenplay Award\n| Caroline Link\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Tokyo Grand Prix\n| Caroline Link\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[Vancouver International Film Festival]]\n| Most Popular Film\n| Caroline Link\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| rowspan=2| [[Young Artist Award]]\n| Best Family Feature - Foreign\n| Caroline Link\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Best Performance in a Foreign Film\n| [[Tatjana Trieb]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=2| 1998\n| [[Academy Awards]]\n| [[Academy Award for Best Foreign Language Film|Best Foreign Language Film]]\n| Caroline Link\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[National Board of Review]]\n| Top Foreign Films\n| Caroline Link\n| {{won}}\n|}\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of submissions to the 70th Academy Awards for Best Foreign Language Film]]\n* [[List of German submissions for the Academy Award for Best Foreign Language Film]]\n* [[List of films featuring the deaf and hard of hearing]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==Book==\n* {{cite book | first = Caroline | last = Link | title = Jenseits der Stille | publisher = Aufbau | year = 2001 | location = Berlin | isbn = 978-3-7466-1453-3 | url-access = registration | url = https://archive.org/details/jenseitsderstill00link }}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20070926221717/http://www.br-online.de/kultur-szene/thema/caroline_link/drehstille.xml Ungew\u00f6hnliche Dreharbeiten] - Bayerischer Rundfunk\n*[http://www.omdb.org/movie/312 Filmeintrag auf omdb.org] with underground information\n* {{IMDb title|0116692|Beyond Silence}}\n\n{{Tokyo Sakura Grand Prix}}\n{{German submission for Academy Awards}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Beyond Silence}}\n[[Category:1996 films]]\n[[Category:Films set in Germany]]\n[[Category:Films set in Berlin]]\n[[Category:German films]]\n[[Category:German-language films]]\n[[Category:German Sign Language films]]\n[[Category:German drama films]]\n[[Category:1990s drama films]]\n[[Category:Films about emotions]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|1996 film}}\n{{use dmy dates|date=October 2015}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name             = Jenseits der Stille\n| image            =\n| director         = [[Caroline Link]]\n| writer           = {{ubl|Caroline Link|[[Beth Serlin]]}}\n| starring       = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Sylvie Testud]]\n* [[Howie Seago]]\n* [[Emmanuelle Laborit]]\n* [[Sibylle Canonica]]\n* [[Matthias Habich]]\n* Hansa Czypionka\n* Tatjana Trieb}}\n| producer         = {{ubl|[[Jakob Claussen]]|[[Thomas W\u00f6bke]]|[[Luggi Waldleitner]]}}\n| released         = {{film date|1996|12|19|df=y}}\n| runtime          = 112 minutes\n| language         = {{ubl|German|[[German Sign Language]]}}\n| budget           =\n| cinematography   = [[Gernot Roll]]\n| music            = [[Niki Reiser]]\n| editing          = [[Patricia Rommel]]\n| country          = Germany\n| gross            = $11.5 million<ref>http://www.jpbox-office.com/fichfilm.php?id=3318</ref>\n}}\n'''''Beyond Silence''''' ({{lang-de|'''Jenseits der Stille'''}}) is a 1996 German film directed by [[Caroline Link]]. The film was nominated for the [[Academy Award for Best Foreign Language Film]] at the [[70th Academy Awards]].<ref name=\"Oscars1998\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.oscars.org/oscars/ceremonies/1998 |title=The 70th Academy Awards (1998) Nominees and Winners |accessdate=13 October 2015 |work=oscars.org}}</ref>\n\n==Plot==\nThe film tells the story of Lara, who grows up as the daughter of [[deaf]] parents, Martin and Kai. Lara herself is hearing and is fluent in [[sign language]]. Even as a young child, she serves as an [[interpreter]] for her parents in many situations, such as credit negotiations at the bank as well as her own parent-teacher conference, although not always completely truthfully.\n\nLara receives a [[clarinet]] for Christmas from Clarissa, her father's sister and an enthusiastic musician. Lara discovers the world of music, where her parents cannot follow her. In the years that follow, she is discovered to be a talented clarinet player.\n\nAfter Kai is killed in a bicylce accident, Lara's grieving father feels abandoned. When 18-year-old Lara wants to study at a music conservatory in Berlin, the family seems to break apart. The ending seems to reconcile it all: Martin tries to understand the love of music that his daughter feels, and the film comes to a careful reunion between him and Lara.\n\n== Cast ==\n{{cast listing|\n* [[Sylvie Testud]] as Lara\n* Tatjana Trieb as young Lara\n* [[Howie Seago]] as Martin\n* [[Emmanuelle Laborit]] as Kai\n* [[Sibylle Canonica]] as Clarissa\n* [[Matthias Habich]] as Gregor (Clarissa's husband)\n* Alexandra Bolz as Marie\n* Hansa Czypionka as Tom\n* [[Doris Schade]] as Lilli\n* [[Horst Sachtleben]] as Robert\n* Hubert Mulzer as Mister G\u00e4rtner\n* [[Birge Schade]] as Miss Mertens\n* [[Stephan Kampwirth]] as Bank Manager\n}}\n\n==Reviews==\n''Beyond Silence'' has an 83% approval rating on [[Rotten Tomatoes]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/beyond_silence/ |title=Beyond Silence (1996) |publisher=Rotten Tomatoes |accessdate=January 10, 2017}}</ref>\n* \"A successful film debut of a graduate of the Munich Film Academy. The film is a sensible presentation of the problem of the handicapped as well as the universal theme of the self discovery of a young woman and the plea for understanding and openness about seemingly disproportionate experiences.\" (film-dienst 25/1996)\n* \"Whoever would like to find out how loud the snow is and how the sounds of a clarinet can enchant people, should not allow themselves to miss this film: a German production which takes up extraordinary themes across the relationship-comedy and tells the story about saying goodbye to one's childhood with gentle humor and an idiosyncratic aesthetic.\" (Fischer Film Almanach, 1997)\n* \"A film that allows silence to become music and has found strength in the balance between laughing and crying, happiness and pain. \"Jenseits der Stille\" is memorable among German productions, and excellently cast. (Dirk Jasper FilmLexikon)\n* \"Thanks to good casting for all roles and assured acting performances under its direction, this [film is] a successful journey into the world of the deaf, with all its problems of social integration and family conflict.\" (FBW Langfilme)\n\n==Accolades==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Award !! Category !! Recipient !! Result\n|-\n| rowspan=16| 1997\n| rowspan=2| [[Bavarian Film Awards]]\n| [[Bavarian Film Awards (Best Director)|Best Director]]\n| [[Caroline Link]]\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[Bavarian Film Awards (Best Film Score)|Best Film Score]]\n| [[Niki Reiser]]\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| rowspan=2| [[Chicago International Film Festival]]\n| Special Mention\n| Caroline Link\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Best Film\n| Caroline Link\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=5| [[Deutscher Filmpreis]]\n| Best Performance by an Actress in a Leading Role\n| [[Sylvie Testud]]\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Best Editing\n| Niki Reiser \n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Outstanding Feature Film\n| Caroline Link\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Best Performance by an Actress in a Supporting Role \n| [[Emmanuelle Laborit]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Best Direction\n| Caroline Link\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Guild of German Art House Cinemas\n| German Film\n| Caroline Link\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[Palm Springs International Film Festival]]\n| Best Foreign Language Film\n| Caroline Link\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=2| [[Tokyo International Film Festival]]\n| Best Screenplay Award\n| Caroline Link\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Tokyo Grand Prix\n| Caroline Link\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[Vancouver International Film Festival]]\n| Most Popular Film\n| Caroline Link\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| rowspan=2| [[Young Artist Award]]\n| Best Family Feature - Foreign\n| Caroline Link\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Best Performance in a Foreign Film\n| [[Tatjana Trieb]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=2| 1998\n| [[Academy Awards]]\n| [[Academy Award for Best Foreign Language Film|Best Foreign Language Film]]\n| Caroline Link\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[National Board of Review]]\n| Top Foreign Films\n| Caroline Link\n| {{won}}\n|}\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of submissions to the 70th Academy Awards for Best Foreign Language Film]]\n* [[List of German submissions for the Academy Award for Best Foreign Language Film]]\n* [[List of films featuring the deaf and hard of hearing]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==Book==\n* {{cite book | first = Caroline | last = Link | title = Jenseits der Stille | publisher = Aufbau | year = 2001 | location = Berlin | isbn = 978-3-7466-1453-3 | url-access = registration | url = https://archive.org/details/jenseitsderstill00link 